1 PART II. UPDATE CERTAIN WORKERS' COMPENSATION BENEFITS
2 SECTION 2.1.(a) G.S. 97-29 reads as rewritten:
3 "§ 97-29. Rates and duration of compensation for total incapacity.
4 (a) When an employee qualifies for total disability, the employer shall pay or cause to be
5 paid, as hereinafter provided by subsections (b) through (d) of this section, to the injured
6 employee a weekly compensation equal to sixty-six and two-thirds percent (66 2/3%) of his
7 average weekly wages, but not more than the amount established annually to be effective January
8 1 as provided herein, nor less than thirty dollars ($30.00) fifty dollars ($50.00) per week.
9 Beginning July 1, 2026, and annually thereafter, the North Carolina Industrial Commission shall
10 raise the maximum compensation herein in accordance with the percentage change in the June
11 Consumer Price Index computed by the Bureau of Labor Statistics and the June Consumer Price
12 Index for the prior year, provided that this percentage change is positive. The adjustment shall
13 be rounded to the nearest dollar ($1.00)."
14 SECTION 2.1.(b) This section becomes effective July 1, 2026.
